## Section Breakdown

### Page Header

- **Title:** The page name ("Dashboard") plus an optional subtitle (e.g. "Last 30 days")
- **Actions (top-right):** Date range picker, refresh button, export button
- Primary actions are always top-right on desktop; collapse into a menu on mobile

### KPI Cards

Show 3-5 key metrics. Each card contains:

- Metric name (short, 2-4 words)
- Current value (formatted: currency, count, percentage)
- Trend indicator: delta from previous period (+ green / - red)
- Sparkline or trend arrow (optional)

{% if design_style == "minimal-clean" %}
**Style guidance (minimal-clean):**
- Cards use a clean white background with a subtle border
- Numbers are large and prominent (`text-3xl font-bold`)
- Trend delta is small, muted, below the main figure
- No decorative icons or gradients
{% elif design_style == "corporate-professional" %}
**Style guidance (corporate-professional):**
- Cards have a light grey background with a left border accent in brand blue
- Metric name in all-caps small text above the number
- Trend shown with an up/down arrow icon and percentage text
- Consistent spacing, no rounded corners
{% elif design_style == "playful-modern" %}
**Style guidance (playful-modern):**
- Cards have a subtle gradient background unique to each metric
- Metric icon (emoji or SVG) in top-right corner
- Number is large with a bouncy font weight
- Trend badge with rounded pill styling
{% endif %}

### Primary Chart

A full-width (or 60% width) chart showing the main trend over the selected time range.

**Choices:**
- Time-series data: Line chart or area chart
- Categorical comparison: Bar chart
- Part-to-whole: Donut chart (avoid pie charts)

**Implementation notes:**
- Use `recharts` or `chart.js` via a wrapper component in `src/components/ui/`
- Chart data is fetched server-side where possible; on the client via TanStack Query with a skeleton fallback
- Always render an empty state when there is no data (never an empty chart area)

### Secondary Charts / Top Items

- Smaller supporting visualisations (right column on desktop, below primary on mobile)
- "Top 5 X" lists are often more useful than a second chart
- Use a simple ranked list with a small bar or percentage beside each item

### Recent Activity Feed

A reverse-chronological list of the last N events.

Each item includes:
- Action description (e.g. "Alice created invoice #1042")
- Timestamp (relative: "3 minutes ago"; absolute on hover)
- Optional: entity link, avatar, or status badge

**Implementation:** Loaded client-side with polling or WebSocket. Use `aria-live="polite"` if auto-updating.

